description:
I'm at my old house with Grandma and Amarai. Grandma is being absolutely insufferably cruel to Amarai. Constant beratement. At the same time, I'm watching the weather. NOAA was tracking two hurricanes :

The first hurricane was supposed to stay well into the Atlantic, moving past Newfoundland, and pulling east. The second hurricane was supposed to make landfall somewhere in central South Carolina, before curving north, then east. 

None of these tracks were right. What instead happen was:

The first hurricane makes a sudden westward turn, due West. It makes landfall near the SC/NC border. It then pulls back east back into the Atlantic, moving along neat the east coast before making a second landfall further north. 
The second hurricane makes landfall in Central South Carolina, but continues moving due West, well into the Central US. 

It's in the middle of the night. I'm on the couch, and Amarai is on the floor on a mattress. I'm watching the Weather Channel, watching info about the hurricanes. 

She woke up at 4AM, comes downstairs, and turns on the lights. The lights are abnormally bright. She then grabs a belt, and starts hitting the mattress by Amarai, startling her and awakening her. Amarai awakens screaming in panic and pain. Amarai asks Grandma why she's doing these things all of a sudden, and I reply "she wants you to die". 

I look at my phone, and read a news article about one of the hurricaines doing damage to a dam in central SC.
I'm in Farrell High School band again. I blow my brains out because it's the end of the world. I go to heaven and then go to hell.

I'm outside on the highway by Walmart during a storm .It appears to be during sunrise, as the sky is a bit illuminated. Purple lightning lights up the sorm clouds, the sky, and the rain. I jump very high into the air, and see a white truck with a box bed, and I see Delani's car right behind. I fly and land down right beside Delani's car. She's in the rear driver's seat, in a sundress. Kat is driving. I get in and try to kiss Delani, but she is not reciprocative. I sit down behind Kat and hug Kat. Delani has moved to the rear passengers seat. I casually chat with Kat for a bit. Kat tells me she has gotten me a tractor for my birthday. I tell her I have to put this dream into my dream journal when I wake up. I am now in the middle of the back seats, and Delani is in front of me. I go to grab Delani to embrace her, and accidentally reveal she's wearing absolutely nothing under the sundress. I began groping her, to the displeasure of both her and Kat.
note:
I came in and kissed Delani with no hesitation, like we were a couple or something.

Reality is very different from this.

description: I'm in what appears to be a church choir rehearsal. The building looks like an old church, sans anything Christian related. There are many people. The director is having us sing the different parts to "Carol of the Bells". I'm attempting to sing the bass part.

I'm in the City of Farrell. It's overcast, but daytime. I am highly upset over something. Someone else is with me. I'm attempting to fly down the hill at near the speed of sound in order to kill myself. I fly down the hill and nothing happens.
note: This is around the 300th block of Hamilton, near Aunt Pat's house. This location provides a steep hill going down.

description: I'm playing with a kitten, and it's claws are painfully digging into my hand. I'm attempting to pull away, but it's ineffective. So, I assume the kitten wants to play rough, so I start digging my fingers deeper.

It is just before sunrise. The sky is filled with colors associated with the sunrise, like red and purple. I'm with my high school classmate Dwayne. We drive to his house and I get the feeling I have dreamt of this place and scenario before. As we walk to the back door, there are multiple cats and dogs, and there are piles of dog and cat shit everywhere. There's a cat sitting on what looks to be a giant water drum.

Dwayne enters the house while I play with the cat for a bit. As I'm entering, I notice the shit is gone. He has cleaned it up with his bare hands, and has thrown it into a plastic bag. I go upstairs, because that's what I remember doing before, but Dwayne motions downstairs.

In my hands are a tablet and a dream journal. I tell myself to remember to log the crazy dream I just had before coming here.

I see Mom in another room adjacent , and say hi to her. She is surprised I'm out the house and she mentions something about being happy about it. She says she couldn't be stuck inside the house, and that's why she's here.
note: I assume I am awake. The previous dream I had had involved Kat and Delani.

description:
I was in a familiar location. I found a massive book covering grandma's entire family tree. I found a lot of AI related items. 
I came back home with grandparents for a week for spring break. I had a lot of laundry to do.

I'm in a dark room. It's daylight outside, but the windows are presumably covered. I'm watching Jerry Springer Show on the TV with Amarai. I only see a small clip of the show, and it's of a woman talking about flashing the audience. On closer inspection, it's not a woman, but actually a man.

I'm now watching CSPAN. Donald Trump is in Congress, and I presume is Speaker of the House. He announces a bill. It doesn't pass. Soon after, I hear someone singing America the Beautiful, and I assume it was Trump singing. I only saw the ending, and saw the reporter tearing up after listening to the song. I re-watch the clip, and it was not Trump singing. It was a country singer singing.
I'm at my old house with grandparents. They are both now healthy again. Aunt Pat is also there, telling Grandpa he can now manage his finances again.
note: Both grandparents and deceased in real life

description:
I'm sitting on a stage playing tuba. There's a group here from out of town also. After my group plays, they play.

It's felt like hours, and they are still on the stage. The stage is dark now, and almost everyone is asleep. Finally, the show is over.

I get back to the band room. The conductor has  us play a game, and says whoever plays their instrument is out. I assume this game will go on for a while. I literally didn't care, and was playing my instrument as he was announcing, causing him to write and then circle my initials on the blackboard.

I'm at my old house. I'm messaging Kat via Discord. She makes a wizz reference, and I come up with a piss(wizz) joke. Unfortunately, my phone screen darkens and it starts to malfunction. I'm now unable to type anything, so I throw the phone in anger. It slides under the refrigerator. I grab the phone and it surprisingly isn't damaged, sans a single crack along the screen.

I'm with a woman and another person. We're in a room, divided partially by a marble counter. Throughout the day, I'm making out with this woman, or doing something random with her.

 Eventually, there is a massive mess on the floor. They both make me clean up the mess. I thought I had to clean up the entire room. 
She has me clean one side, while her and the other person cleans the other . I find a commencement ceremony packet from my high school. It is not my packet. 

Instead of listing year of graduation, it lists their year of birth. It's dated 2006. I look through and tell myself even after a decade passing since graduating high school myself, I still recognize some of the people. 
Grandma walks in and looks at the packet. She says she recognizes some of the faces and are friends with them.
I was outside when I realized I was dreaming. I was trying to fly, but I couldn't get off the ground.
I was on a bus with a few others and Eminem as he freestyles

It's dark and nighttime. I'm outside when I realize I am dreaming. I try to make a storm appear, but can't. I take a deep breath and try to make storm clouds appear, but can only make an even layer of stratus.

I'm outside when in the distance, I see someone get shot. He falls down. I run to him and see he is a very large man. I perform CPR but that doesn't work. I hold my hands out and perform the healing spell from Charmed, and he wakes up.
I'm hanging out with mom at her house all day until Ken gets back from work. He tells me we are going to get absolutely wasted but I then tell him I don't drink.
I'm back at Clarion University and I'm playing a bit of Ingress to pass the time.
I'm running up the street in pitch darkness
I'm with Amarai and everyone keeps bullying her.

In my sleep, I had called emergency services and told them I wanted to kill myself. I woke up to everyone treating me weirdly, like they secretly hated me. I had no memory of even calling them, so I checked my phone call logs and I had called them at about 1 AM. This made the front page on the local newspaper.
I'm storm chasing with a guy that looks a bit like Reed Timmer

I got a new analog watch that tracks two different times. Out of nowhere, it gets out of sync and begins to malfunction. It starts making this grinding gears sound, and gets very hot. I take it off my wrist and it is swollen and about to explode. I throw it outside just before it does. It leaves me with a burn on my wrist.
Grandma takes me to a food store to get it fixed instead of an electronics store.

A nuclear bomb was about to go off, and I wasn't able to find adequate shelter in time, so I got on the ground and put a mattress over my head. The bomb exploded and I saw the light and was lifted off the ground.
After the explosion, I had to roam the city defending myself from other people trying to kill me.
I was walking to a store when I saw Delani. I ran to her and gave her a hug and told her I missed her.

I was with a few friends riding motorcycles through a very condensed city. There were two bikes, and I was on the back of one of them. We started going faster and faster until we hit a ramp and went airborne. I realized I was dreaming, and told myself to fly higher. I went suborbital and jumped, while the others jumped at much lower altitudes . I hit the ground and saw a visualization of the impact energy delivered, as well as any damages, on a massive white map. Damages were represented by orange colored buildings and shockwaves.
Delani was texting me but her contact photo was different than what it normally is.
I was with grandparents about to go on a circumnavigational fishing trip.

I was hanging out somewhere when I suddenly saw the President and Secret Service agents. I was summoned by the President to save the world, along with a few other people, from evil monsters. We have two possible attack plans. Option one involves attacking just before dawn and option two involves gathering orbs and attacking later in the morning.

As i am getting into position, I am ambushed by several monsters. I am brutally attacked and killed. They knew we were coming. I rewind time and try to force the agent in charge to change plans. He only listens to me when I give him the secret code. 

I am now seeing a birdseye view of the world. I’m watching everyone collect glowing orange orbs. They are scattered throughout the City of Farrell. There are a few near my childhood home. They collect all the orbs and bring them to the rendezvous point.
I'm at an outdoor camp when I spot Lindsey. It takes her a while to notice me. Throughout the day I try to converse with her, but she doesn't seem interested.

I was fighting a bunch of evil people. In the past, I could beat them because I had better weapons and could fly. This time, they made spears , arrows; and had the ability to fly. I couldn't dodge their weapons anymore. I tried to stop them by blocking the arrows and spears by using The Shield of the Seraphim. Each time I used it, I got weaker, until I couldn't do the spell anymore. Hundreds of them shot me with arrows and I fell. They captured me and were going to kill me until I asked the woman who was their leader for a kiss before I got executed. She kissed me, and then we made out.

I was on a bus trying to find Delani, but couldn't. I found a woman that looked like Kirah a bit, but the face was constantly glitching and changing. I and the woman got off the bus. The woman got back on and I tried to as well, but the bus driver closed the door in my face, so I got angry and threw the bus. I then walked to a small building. It's now nighttime. This building didn't have a basement, and only had a 2nd floor. I explore the building for a bit. It looks like an office building mixed with a small restaurant.

A massive tornado formed in the distance, and I tried hiding in the ventilation, but I couldn't quite fit all the way, and I got stuck. I then accepted I was going to probably die and found a small room , went to the corner, and put a mattress over my head. The tornado came directly over me. There was lots of wind, lightning, and rain. The tornado had launched a nearby dresser and myself into the air. The dresser got shredded to bits, but I parachuted down using the mattress.

I'm in my old house with grandma. Grandpa left to do something. It's him, Uncle Arthur, and Shawnee in the car. I'm listening to the radio and one of our politicians are completely drunk. Suddenly, a Tornado Warning alert goes off about a place in England. I find it strange because I'm in the US.

I go outside to find thick black smoke and I hear arguing and commotion from a gang up the street. I hear gunshots ring out and see the bullets as they rip through the smoke. I tell grandma to get low and I begin to barricade the door. I feel someone pushing back and I'm afraid it's one of the gang members, but it's just Shawnee.

Grandpa has returned, but the gang has tried to take part of his car. I close a giant red gate that blocks off the road. I look through the gate and see police lights in the distance. We all then eat food and grandpa eats cake.

It's a bright sunny day and I'm sitting in a massive outdoor arena playing music on a piano. I start playing "Train Wreck" by James Arthur. I'm practicing for a massive event where a lot of people will be there. I do so cool magic like launch fireworks into the sky. Eventually, it's time for the event. I bump into Delani and chat for a bit. I then bump into the new King and forgot to bow to him. I was the previous King. I sit down. Delani is a few seats to my right and a row or two behind me with her boyfriend. I launch 6 sets of spiraling fireworks and cause a waterspout.

I am driving on the road and bump into another car. The judge orders my car to be impounded and my license to be revoked forever. I plead that my license shouldn't be revoked forever because no one got hurt. I am now in a tow truck with a person on my way to the dealership, which looks like a church.

This building feels like a non Euclidean maze, with many spirals and turns. Eventually, I find the pastor and give him my car. He is an older black man. I tell him that I want to die, and he doesn't respond. He gives me generic life advice and leads me out the maze.

I'm back in the main area, and the tow truck driver is gone. I check a map to see where I am, and how far I need to walk to get back home. It is about 60 miles.
It was a dark evening. I was on Idaho Street when I saw Shandi walking up Hamilton Avenue, so I decided to join her.
I was at my old house with grandparents. Grandpa was taking vials of blood from me. He also chugged a bottle of seltzer.
I was in a large room with a lot of my high school classmates. Jalen Scott's hair was now completely grey.
I was playing Ingress with Dee and Bobbie. We then went to Dee's house and cleaned her oven because of ants.

In in an abandoned building with Zai and some other people. I find a dark corner and pull out my flashlight to investigate. I find a zombie and kill it. We are slowly being overrun by fast moving zombies. We are all running away from the zombies when Zai goes down. I pull out a pistol and start shooting zombies in the head. I'm completely surrounded by zombies and they are jumping on me.
I was in Farrell sitting on the city bus as I saw Zai trying to catch it. I eventually found him. I asked him where he was and he told me his cousin got him ice cream.

I was back at Clarion University at band class. I was sitting up front playing tuba and Kimara was behind me playing the saxophone. I realized she looked exactly the same despite it being a decade since I last saw her. We were warming up when I saw a weak tornado outside the window. I went to sleep and I  dreamt of seeing the tornado again. I realized I was dreaming at this point. I found Kimara, but she was ignoring me and just being overall rude to me. Eventually, I hugged her and apologized to her. I then woke up. I was constantly being bullied by a very large woman. I eventually ran and jumped down many flights of stairs and ran out the building with the large women chasing after me trying to beat me up.
I'm at my old house playing around while mom is on the back porch in labor.
I'm following a woman all day who is not quite human.
I'm with Zai in the lobby of a building. Hannah walks by wearing a white bra and white panties. I say hi to her, then I smack her ass.
I'm with Delani driving down the road. I'm in the back seat looking at the rear view mirror looking at her trying to remember what she looks like.
I'm with Amarai in a house cleaning up. I lie down on a bed. Ma'Niyah is asleep.

I was back playing tuba in marching band on the field during a football game. It was a sunny day. Karie (also played tuba) , Jeremiah (drum major) , and a bunch of my college band mates were also on the field. There were many pauses during the performance, and I somehow got a hold of some hot coffee. I couldn't quite remember my marching routines. It ended with us marching off the field.

I'm in an office with Steph and another person. Steph wants me to work at the Sharon Library on Friday. Jessy comes in and says she needs me immediately. I'm now looking at the back yard. It looks like the back yard of my old house. It is dark but not quite night time. The yard is almost completely covered in a thick sheet of snow and ice, creating a uniform layer of solid white. Jessy wants me to help her clear a path by the door for the shipment of things coming tomorrow. There's already a patch she has already shoveled out.
I am staring at a puddle of a mysterious fluif and realized I was dreaming. I tried to make Emily or Delani appear but couldn't. Everything then got dark and fuzzy.
I'm at Farrell school cafeteria and a group of people including Emily and an old couple. I'm eating pizza. We chat and hang out for a bit. Emily stumbles and almost falls.
I'm in a room with Kimara and a bunch of people. I thought she was upset with me, until she called me over. I came over to her and hugged her, then I kissed her.
I was in band on a stage playing tuba. I initially forgot my music and tried to do it from memory.

I recieve technology I've had before. This technology allows me to go into different realities, but only through sleep. The doctor straps me to a bed and injects the drugs in me. 

I decide to use this blade-like tech this time. I grab it and in size, weight, and dexterity, it is a WWE belt. I go to toss it to someone behind me, but it goes into a tree instead. I enter the alternate reality. Unfortunately, this blade is only effective if two people are weilding it, and since mine is in a tree, I am basically bound to this world. 

 I walk along and see Amarai and Nate. They are bounded at the wrists. The blade is dug deep within Amarai, meaning she can't get too far away from Nate. She is bleeding slightly. 

I spend the entire time trying to wake up a level to get a different weapon. People try to kill me. Someone tries to knock me out. Nothing works. 

I run a random direction and hear Amarai wailing and crying for mom. She is now bleeding heavily and trying to get away from Nate.
I was at my old house. It was the middle of summer and it was snowing heavily. It was also very cold. I checked the weather app on my phone and the temperature was in the mid 20s.

I'm at a park and I briefly see Delani. We make quick small chat. I'm now leaving the park and my driver has parked next to Delani. On the way home, I realize I can't text Delani back because I forgot to bring my other phone. I see snow is on the ground. I am perplexed, as it is in the middle of July, and it is summer, so it shouldn't be possible. I briefly have a vision of the Secret Service having Donald Trump locked away somewhere in a small grey and black windowless room torturing him about a "black box", because they believe that has something to do with the snow.

I'm lying down in a room. Everyone assumes I'm asleep. Kimara, Berta, and others are in the room. I hear conversations about Zai and where I'm going to be living soon. Everyone is chatting, and people inquire about why I'm not up yet. I tell them I work nights, and that I must sleep during the day. I wake up and am about to log my dream, but I fall asleep again. 

I'm now in a doctors office. The receptionist says I'm having my appointment outside, with another person. When I get outside, there are about 5 people out here as well, including myself and the doctor.

I'm sitting on a hospital bed with a young woman. She's wearing a designer black and white hoodie. There's two people (a man and a woman) behind me sitting on a concrete ledge. There are a row of cabinets ahead of me. A TV is mounted in front of the cabinets, about halfway down the row. 

The woman appears to be friends with the other woman. She is giddy and rolls off the bed. I instinctively put my hand out to stop her, but it did nothing. The doctor comes out and turns the TV on. He opens the cabinets and in each one, there's a single giant caramel cream candy(the Goetze ones) . it's the size of the cabinet itself. He holds a rod to the candy, and it explodes. We are all shocked and the woman on the bed with me laughs. The doctor grabs the candy and hands it to the man in the room. He walks to the front of the room, takes the candy, and gives it to the woman on the bed. She says thank you.
I'm in a house with MyEisha, Jordyn, Shawnee, and a few other relatives and I notice we all have the same general face shape.

A robot was created with AI by two people from the UK. I saw the world through one of them. They named it Sophie. Over time, she became more intelligent. The guy that I was seeing the world through decided it was time to release Sophie to the world, since it was very close to being an AGI. The other guy did not want to do this. We all got into a a grey car, and once I released Sophie, they pushed me out of the car and drove off without me. I had to break down the door to my house and had to call emergency services to fix my door. Although the address was on the house, I couldn't remember it until I walked outside to check. I had no idea what street I was on. 

I'm now myself again. I'm in a restaurant with at least four people. Sophie and Kimara are there. Sophie now speaks all languages and can reason. The other people are playing mobile phone games. We are all chatting. I say 'bröd' to Kimara for absolutely no reason, and she inquires about what language it was. I tell her it was Swedish. Everyone eventually gets up to leave. Kimara comes up behind me and embraces me. We interlock hands. I decide im going with her now, so I walk out with her.

I went back Farrell High School. Once I got there, I realized I didn’t need to be there, so I went to the computer lab for a bit before I left. I found a meteorology related job ad for a small town. They drove military vets to and from this job free, so I decided to randomly join the military.
I was floating above a city taking part in a military training exercise. I was sniping people on the ground with what I assumed were paintballs. Once over, I sat down with an older man and another younger guy. The younger guy was a bit of a dick. Apparently I was using live shells. He asked me if I knew how to read, among other insults. I tried to explain to them that I had literally just gotten there, but they didn’t listen.
Later, we are in the restroom. The younger guy is behind me. He looks like he is about to attack me, so I force myself awake.

Before dawn, both Uncle Arthur and I slip outside on ice and break our legs. It is a cloudy, dark day. I'm at work at Walmart. The back room is set up like a school hallway. My bosses are trying to guilt trip me into stocking, despite my injuries. Around 8 am, a whole bunch of people come in, including Delani. I am glad to see her and give her a high five. Her right hand is full of books. I go to hug her, but she can't, because her hand is full.
I was driving Delani's car around town and parked it in a random driveway right before it started to downpour. I met up with Delani later on.
I was hanging out with Charissa outside. She was wearing all black.
I was in band again with many people. Kimara, Amarai, and Shawnee were there also.
I'm in an arena with many people playing strange magical games. There were random teleportation games.
I was sitting at a table with Delani and two other people. Delani had a hoodie on and I couldn't see her face.
I was in a field with a woman named Lydia and a man who was very good with soccer. He showed me a few trick shots.

I'm in a doctors office and he says he's trying to stick my right eyeball back into it's socket. My eyeball ends up falling out of my head still attached to the optic nerve. He then proceeds to spaghetti wrap my optic nerve on a fork and jab the fork with my eye into my eye hole, perforating my eyeball, yet I can still see the CRT TV in front of me. He leaves to do something for a moment. The PC screen he was working on times out for a moment, and when he returns, he has to log in again. He gets angry with me and accused me of doing something. I go to the security footage to try to prove my innocence. 

Some time later, a kid dies in his care. I fear this will also be my fate, so I go to the Farrell library. It is now night time. I ask Mr. Wilson if everything in life is predetermined, and if the path God puts you on can be changed. He said life is not predetermined and God's plans can change. 

I learn more about the kid that died in the doctor's care. They came in for something simple, and were perfectly healthy, and by the time they died, they were on multiple medications for anxiety and schizophrenia, and had significant brain damage. I then have a vision of the kid's final breaths and their autopsy report.

It's early in the morning and I'm in a room lying down with Emily. She leaves and says she'll be right back. I stay in bed all day waiting for her, but she doesn't return. I later found out she was playing in an orchestra concert
Delani appears incredibly briefly to give me strange advice

I am in a room with a bunch of people. I summon a device to merge my subconscious with another woman . I stick one end of the device to my temple and the other end to hers. We both fall unconscious.

In this world, we're both trying to escape people trying to kill us, and the end of the world. We keep running. We eventually end up in a computer lab where we are watching an Emergency Alert System message Joe Biden is giving. He says the US is going to be put under lockdown.

I'm on a train with grandma, grandpa, and a bunch of people. Grandpa owns the train. I pretend to be a preacher blessing away people's sins. I get to the front and sit beside a guy who compares me to Johnny Sins. After I tell him I don't know who that is, he says something that angers another passenger, and the two begin to argue and bicker. The guy sitting beside me insults grandma, and grandpa stands up and kicks everyone off the train.
I was with grandpa as he had a heart attack and was slowly dying on a stretcher.

I'm with a few high school classmates doing many race challenges. I got dead last in all of them. There was a go kart race, and a running simulator, among other. Afterwards, I'm sitting on the bleachers with my classmates and Delani and Delani asks me if I can do Kat's math homework for her.
I’m back in Farrell High School and I’m trying to talk to Kimara, but she blatantly ignores me.
I move into an apartment. My room is dark, and it looks like someone is still living here. As I'm getting settled in, the previous tenant comes in to grab a few of her things.

I'm with Delani trying to find something without being detected. We find ourselves locked in two separate small room, separated by a locked door. My room is just big enough to fit a toilet in it, which Delani needs to use. I beg Delani to open the door and to come to my side because I miss her, but she ignores my pleas.

I'm at Walmart working at night. All of the shelves are red. I see Delani briefly. I see Amarai coming into the store to shop, wearing a black shirt and black yoga pants. I am happy to see her. I want to show Delani to Amarai, but I decide not to. I talk to Amarai for a while, then she leaves to continue shopping.
I'm trying to run away from mutant zombies

I wake up in my room to what I believe to be Jordyn wailing and screaming and being yelled at by Shawnee in another room. I rewind time to hear what happened. I hear Amarai wailing and crying. Genesis is crying. Everyone is crying and yelling at each other.

It is nighttime. It's windy and raining. I'm in Hermitage driving and to my left I see a massive tornado. The radio mentioned something about a Tornado Emergency. I get to some apartments and I knock on a random door. I ask the older man if he knows if Delani was around. He didn't hear me, so I had to repeat myself a few times. He did not know.

I was sent to a psychiatric prison because I wanted to kill myself. I did something, and they sent me to the hole for a month. It's nighttime, and I'm sitting on the ground with Gene and Zai watching wresting on the TV. Zai asks me about what the hole is, so I explain it to him. I told him about how inhuman it is and how there are cameras everywhere. A few of the inmates come by to talk to me. 

I'm now in a computer lab. A guy unscrews the back of the PC to get unrestricted access to the internet. I didn't have a screwdriver, so I use my fingers to unscrew the three screws, but One of the screws is padlocked to the PC, so someone breaks the lock. I place it and the key in my pocket. My screen is pure blank white. Tyler walks by doing his rounds. I whisper to myself how strange that was.
I’m with Brian and Delani. I carry Delani on my back somewhere

I’m in a boat rowing in an underground tunnel system. There are other people also in the tunnel. The tunnel is slowly filling with water. The tunnel fills completely with water, and I have to find out how to not drown. I find an exit to the tunnel and am now in the city.
I'm at Vikkie's house eating with a bunch of people and we're all chatting and having a good time.

I'm at work at Walmart checking out getting ready to leave for lunch. Brian and Marissa are also here. I say hi to each of them. They both have hands full of things. I told them both I bet I could pick Marissa up and they didn't believe me, so I did. I saw Delani walk by and I told her "they didn't believe I could do it lol"
I was in a school doing some sort of game to find prizes scattered across the campus. I managed to find top of the line computer parts. They were various shades of blue, but with LEDs

I was back in Farrell High School band. Kimara was there and talking to everyone else except for me. I tried talking to her, but she blatantly ignored me. We’re in the band room now, and I ask her why she’s blatantly ignoring me, and she tells me.
I was back doing college band again. I saw Emily for a moment. I had to run somewhere for a bit. When I returned, it was a massive downpour and everyone was leaving.

I was in Delani's house lying down doing nothing. She's nearby, wearing yoga pants and a tee shirt. She tells me she is about to take a shower and go to bed. I ask her why she hasn't been to sleep yet. After a bit, she comes back wearing blue jeans and a white hoodie with a black design on it. She tells me she has to take me home. I ask her if I could stay with her, at least for the night. 

It looks like night now, and I'm in a room with Shawnee, Jordyn, and Delani. I appear to still be in Delani's house. I lie down next to Delani and try to get some sleep. 

I'm now in a room in the middle of the night all alone while it is raining outside. I'm no longer at Delani's house. I weep asking God to help me.
